short_description: This three bedroom terrace Victorian house on Huntspill Street is located within close proximity to Tooting Broadway underground station, Earlsfield Main Line Station and Garratt Lane's array of amenities as well as all Tooting has to offer. Wandsworth Common is also close by as is St George's Hospital. A large garden and scope to extend into the loft, side return and rear. A property that is not to be missed by someone looking for a great opportunity!
A superb three bedroom, three bathroom end of terrace house which has been beautifully refurbished with fantastic attention to detail.
A fantastic opportunity to purchase this unextended, 3-bedroom mid-terrace house on a quiet residential street in Tooting. Scope for extension, subject to the necessary permissions.

A well presented four bedroom 1930's maisonette arranged over two floors.  The property has been thoughtfully extended into the loft to create a wonderful family home. Further benefits are a beautifully maintained private garden and is 0.5 miles from Earlsfield mainline station. Entered via its own front door the accommodation which is laid over the first floor and second floor comprises; a reception room which is open plan to the dining area, modern kitchen, family bathroom finished to a good standard, three double bedrooms, stairs lead to the second floor where there is an impressive master bedroom with en suite bathroom and also includes an extremely useful storage area. The property also offers generous amounts of storage in the eaves.The property is situated on the ever popular Magdalen Estate, conveniently located for Beatrix Potter school, Earlsfield railway station and less than 0.7 of a mile from the beautiful wide open spaces of Wandsworth Common.

This mid terrace house would be perfect for someone who wishes to purchase a property where they can put their own stamp on it. It has the potential to be extended out and into the loft, subject to planning. There are currently two reception rooms and three bedrooms and a rear garden. It is in a super location, being very close to Tooting Broadway 24hr Tube station (Northern Line) and the High Street. Close by are gyms, bars and restaurants as well as the well renowned Tooting Market. With no onward chain this is, in our opinion, a great opportunity. London Borough of Wandsworth, Freehold.

Situated in a quiet location between Earlsfield and Tooting, is this four double bedroom house arranged over three elegant floors.
A charming three bedroom semi-detached house with private front and rear garden plus its very own garage with side access on Rogers Road.
Guide price £690,000 - £720,000 chic four-bedroom, two-bathroom Victorian home. Call to view now.

A three bedroom, mid-terraced, Victorian family home that offers the buyer scope to improve and extend a home to their own style and taste. Offered to the market with full vacant possession and no onward chain.

An exciting opportunity to acquire a three-bedroom family house with huge potential to extend into the loft and rear (subject to the necessary planning permission). The property is in need of updating throughout. (contd...)

A three bedroom two bathroom modern build house with a sunny private garden and off street parking in a desirable private mews close to Tooting Broadway Tube and St George's Hospital.Hepdon Mews is a quiet gated community located only a short distance from Tooting Broadway Underground Station. The increasingly popular Tooting Market is nearby, with it's numerous independant cafes, pubs, restaurants and bars.
Fabulous end of terrace freehold house, located in the heart of Earlsfield with easy access to earlsfield mainline station, garrat lane and wandsworth common
This three bedroom end of terrace home is perfectly located within a quiet development between Earlsfield and Tooting.

Situated opposite an open green to the front and tucked away in a quiet spot close to both Earlsfield and Tooting Stations is three bedroom end of terrace family house. A three bedroom terrace house with large garden.  Accommodation consists of a generous entrance hall with useful storage cupboard, spacious kitchen breakfast room, reception room which offers a great entertaining space, three double bedrooms, family bathroom and large garden.The property is situated on Deeside Road, offering easy access to both Earlsfield mainline railway station or Tooting Broadway underground station, with a large array of restaurants and bars within easy reach.
